                <div class="field-content"><p>At this week‚Äôs U.S.-China Climate Leaders Summit in Los Angeles, eleven cities and provinces from across China committed to reach a peak in their carbon dioxide emissions before the national goal to peak around 2030.  The cities and provinces‚Äîalong with eighteen U.S. counterparts, which announced emissions reduction targets‚Äîalso pledged to track and report their emissions, establish climate action plans, and enhance U.S.-China cooperation at the subnational level.</p></div>
